underlying_goal: To commit a large set of changes related to code/doc cleanup and new implementation plans.
primary_success: Intelligently splitting a messy working directory with mixed changes (deletions, modifications, new files) into three distinct, logical commits for cleanup, new plans, and new tests, creating a clean and understandable git history.
brief_summary: The user requested to commit the current work. Claude analyzed changes including deletions of old docs/code, a new implementation plan, and new test files. It intelligently separated these into three logical commits and pushed them to the remote repository.
